rats and dandelions i took my rats outside for free range time today as i often do and being a nice sunny day my little boy bubba happened upon a lovely big yellow dandelion before i had a chance to decide whether or not he should be friendly with it he decapitated the thing and was skipping off to his cage with it bubba has mycoplasmia so i'm wanting to make his time here on earth as fun filled as possible i didn't want to take it from him i know dandelions are fine for cavies so are they fine fro rats because no matter how i searched i couldn't find it you know how rats are i'll find it when i lean out the cage will bubba and harry be ok just a little on bubba bubba is fine he just has some trouble breathing when he gets exited i know why nad i feel so bad when i first got him knowing little to nil about rat keeping i had him in a plastic tank with shavings waaahh it was online at the many rat communities that i learnt how to care fro rats properly i updated the tank changed the lining and got him a brother to be with harry i wish i could go back to that pet shop which i am now nowhere near and tell them a thing or two about how to care for rodents they often let the mouse tank water run out completely before refilling it their excuse was they keep pulling it down and it leaks out well i say no duh they're bored the poor things nothing to do but sleep and play on their water bottle and there were about mice in one of those large plastic fish tanks they don't have any animal care books in stock but plenty of oh so expensive doggy costumes no new owner inductions at all i will be contacting rspca or something to investigate soon from now on it is my intention to only ever adopt rescue rats so i don't support pet shop cruelty what a great responsible owner dandelions safe for rats yep of course if they are from somewhere where no dogs cats cars etc pollute i actually grow their own little patch in the corner of my garden full of dandelions fat hen burdock etc especially so my rats can have the freshest they all love the flowers the best re bubbles and myco did you know god i sound patronising but i dont meant to be that all rats carry myco and a treatment of anti bi's can keep it under control with good housing and bedding no tanks or sawdust your rat will live a normal life expectancy Hamster Fancy rat Guinea pig RuneScape quests Shaggy dog story Garfield EastEnders The Life and Times of Juniper Lee Domestic rabbit Ren and Stimpy Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Cat Chinchilla Dog Little Britain Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) True Crime: Streets of LA Animal rights W.I.T.C.H. Sewage treatment Looney Tunes and Merrie Melodies filmography Poker jargon Ferret Pet store Animal testing The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Humphrey Bogart One Piece minor characters Gaia Online Ron Weasley Dilbert 2000 Australian Grand Prix The Amber Spyglass Pet The Secret of NIMH Tai shogi Naval mine Taboo food and drink Knots Landing Sea-Monkey Brown Rat Autonomous building Rebreather Theory of conduct Richard Rahl Mickey Mouse Rat Park The Catcher in the Rye Pitaten Stop Huntingdon Animal Cruelty Futurama (TV series - season 2) Care Bears The Amazing Maurice and his Educated Rodents Equine conformation Chicken Fish farming Carburetor Days of our Lives Blood (computer game) Kodocha Plastic Aladdin (1992 film) Tire Jon Secada Electrophysiology Punk ideology The Beach Boys Strap-on dildo Ray Bradbury Plame affair The Suffering (game) Characters in the Smurfs Bubble Bobble Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an One Tree Hill (TV series) The Lovely Bones Professional wrestling match types Taikyoku shogi Norway national football team People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals Fruits Basket Satchel Paige Seismic retrofit Superman Hip hop collaborations Urinary incontinence I'm Sorry I Haven't a Clue Aquemini Trailer Park Boys Fox hunting 